PREORDER, INORDER, AND POSTORDER TRAVERSAL IN ONE

You are given a binary tree represented as an array in level order format. Your task is to return three traversals of the binary tree:

Inorder traversal
Preorder traversal
Postorder traversal

Each traversal should be returned as a list of integers.

FUNCTION DESCRIPTION

Function name: getTraversals

This function returns all three traversals of the binary tree.

PARAMETERS

root
Pointer/reference to the root node of the binary tree

RETURN VALUE

Return a 2D list containing three traversals in the following order:
Inorder traversal
Preorder traversal
Postorder traversal

CONSTRAINTS

1 ≤ T ≤ 10
1 ≤ N ≤ 100000
0 ≤ Node value ≤ 100000
-1 represents a null node

INPUT FORMAT

The first line contains an integer T, the number of test cases

For each test case:
The first line contains an integer N
The second line contains N space-separated integers representing the tree in level order
-1 represents a null node

OUTPUT FORMAT

Print the result in the following format:
[ [Inorder], [Preorder], [Postorder] ]

SAMPLE INPUT

1
7
10 5 15 3 7 -1 18

SAMPLE OUTPUT

[[3, 5, 7, 10, 15, 18], [10, 5, 3, 7, 15, 18], [3, 7, 5, 18, 15, 10]]

EXPLANATION

The tree is:

    10  
   /  \  
  5    15  
 / \     \  
3   7     18  

Inorder traversal: 3 5 7 10 15 18
Preorder traversal: 10 5 3 7 15 18
Postorder traversal: 3 7 5 18 15 10

SAMPLE INPUT

1
7
1 2 3 -1 -1 4 5

SAMPLE OUTPUT

[[2, 1, 4, 3, 5], [1, 2, 3, 4, 5], [2, 4, 5, 3, 1]]

SAMPLE INPUT

1
11
8 4 10 2 6 9 12 -1 -1 5 7

SAMPLE OUTPUT

[[2, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 10, 12], [8, 4, 2, 6, 5, 7, 10, 9, 12], [2, 5, 7, 6, 4, 9, 12, 10, 8]]
Explanation:
The binary tree is:

          8
        /   \
       4     10
      / \    / \
     2   6  9  12
        / \
       5   7
In-order: [2, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 10, 12]
Pre-order: [8, 4, 2, 6, 5, 7, 10, 9, 12]
Post-order: [2, 5, 7, 6, 4, 9, 12, 10, 8]


class Solution {

    private void inorder(TreeNode root, List<Integer> res) {
        if(root==null) return;
        inorder(root.left,res);
        res.add(root.val).
        inorder(root.right,res);
    } private void preorder(TreeNode root, List<Integer> res) {
        if(root==null) return;
        res.add(root.val);
        preorder(root.left,res);
        preorder(root.right,res);
        res.add(root.val);
    } private void postorder(TreeNode root, List<Integer> res) {
        if(root==null) return;
        postorder(root.left,res);
        postorder(root.right,res);
        res.add(root.val);
    } public List<List<Integer>> getTraversals(TreeNode root) {
        List<Integer> in=new ArrayList<>();
        List<Integer> pre=new ArrayList<>();
        List<Integer> post=new ArrayList<>();
        inorder(root,in);
        preorder(root,pre);
        postorder(root,post);
        List<List<Integer>> list=new ArrayList<>();
        list.add(in);
        list.add(pre);
        list.add(post);
        return list;
    }
}
